<div class="headerbox">
<h3>December 2012</h3>  
</div>
<div>

</div>

<br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="724"><span style="display: none">Get on the Air with Dave Graveline!</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Get on the Air with Dave Graveline!</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/graveline.jpg"/>
<p>&ldquo;<a href="www.intotomorrow.com" target="_blank">Into Tomorrow with Dave Graveline</a>&rdquo; launches their 18<sup>th</sup> year covering consumer technology at the 2013 International CES<sup>&reg;</sup>. If you&rsquo;ll be showing NEW products, be sure to contact Dave&rsquo;s producer. Rob Almanza as soon as possible via <a href="mailto:rob@graveline.com">rob@graveline.com</a> with details of your announcements. They&rsquo;ll have three weeks of CES coverage including video highlights, interviews, even video booth tours and &ldquo;Dave&rsquo;s Top 10 at CES.&rdquo;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="723"><span style="display: none">CNET at CES</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">CNET at CES</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Awards%20and%20Events/2013BestCES_small.gif"/>
<p>CNET, the&nbsp;<em>Official Digital News and Video Partner</em> of CES,&nbsp;will once again deliver the hottest coverage of the show, from the LVCC, South Hall Lobby. Dozens of expert editors will be reporting on keynotes, participating in SuperSessions, giving first looks of new products and canvassing the show floor to select what will be awarded the prestigious Best of CES. If you have a product to show an editor, <a href="http://www.cnet.com/how-to-submit-products-for-review/" target="_blank">get in touch now</a>!</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="729"><span style="display: none">The Technology and Engineering Emmy® Awards </span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">The Technology and Engineering Emmy® Awards </div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Awards%20and%20Events/Emmys_200.gif"/>
<p>Launched in 1948, The Technology and Engineering Emmy<sup>&reg;</sup> Awards honor development and innovation in broadcast technology and recognize companies, organizations and individuals for breakthroughs in technology that have a significant effect on television engineering. The Emmy<sup>&reg;</sup> awards will be presented at CES for the seventh year in a row. For ticket information, contact <a href="mailto:tickets@emmyonline.tv">tickets@emmyonline.tv</a> or 212-484-9414. For sponsorship information, contact <a href="mailto:sponsor@emmyonline.tv">sponsor@emmyonline.tv</a> or 212-484-9414.</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="730"><span style="display: none">What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision Stars of CES</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision Stars of CES</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Awards%20and%20Events/CES-708WHFces2013.jpg"/>
<p>Following the tremendous success of 2012, CES will once again play host to the Stars of CES &ndash; the Awards scheme from <em>What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision</em>, the world&rsquo;s leading home entertainment buyer&rsquo;s guide, showcasing the music- and movie-boosting heroes of the world&rsquo;s most important technology event. Centered on the high-performance audio exhibits in The Venetian, Stars of CES will highlight the show&rsquo;s most impressive debuts, from the latest high-tech streaming solutions to the very best in traditional hi-fi and AV. Potential Stars of CES winners don&rsquo;t need a big booth to impress our expert judges &ndash; just a superb new product that will excite our global readership of enthusiasts. <em>What Hi-Fi? Sound and Vision</em> has been sharing its passion for the very best in audio and video for more than 36 years. In January 2013 we&rsquo;ll have even more to shout about. Early product submissions can be sent to <a href="mailto:StarsofCES.awards@haymarket.com">StarsofCES.awards@haymarket.com</a> and include any embargo details clearly.</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="727"><span style="display: none">Submit Your Entry for the Hot Stuff Awards</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Submit Your Entry for the Hot Stuff Awards</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Awards%20and%20Events/2013HotStuff_small.gif"/>
<p>The CES Hot Stuff Awards returns for the third consecutive year, showcasing the 10 most exciting, disruptive and desirable products to launch at the 2013 CES. Judged by <em>Stuff&#39;s</em> team of international editors, the CES Hot Stuff Awards will cover every inch of the show: no gadget, app or service is too diminutive or too grandiose to be considered.&nbsp;<em>Stuff</em> is the world&#39;s best-selling gadget magazine with over 5 million readers worldwide, and has been showcasing the very best tech for almost 15 years. If you think your new launch has what it takes to make the shortlist, early submissions can be sent to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:hotstuff.awards@haymarket.com" target="_blank">hotstuff.awards@haymarket.com</a>&nbsp;&ndash; please include any embargo conditions clearly.</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="728"><span style="display: none">The Official CES Digital Imaging/Photography Daily</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">The Official CES Digital Imaging/Photography Daily</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/diDaily.gif"/>
<p>Promote your organization and drive booth traffic with an ad in the <em>Official CES Digital Imaging/Photography Daily</em>, produced by&nbsp;<em>Photo Industry Reporter</em>. This publication focuses specifically on imaging and features show information, the latest breaking news and industry information. The <em>Official CES Digital Imaging/Photography Daily</em> distribution will occur on-site in numerous high-traffic locations throughout CES, as well as distribution to official PMA-designated hotels each morning of January 8-10. For more information, you can email <a href="mailto:alevine@photoreporter.com">alevine@photoreporter.com</a> or visit <a href="http://www.PhotoReporter.com">www.PhotoReporter.com</a>.</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="722"><span style="display: none">Be Seen by the Entertainment/Content Community</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Be Seen by the Entertainment/Content Community</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/Logos/CES-336_Weekly-Variety-RED_225pw.jpg"/>
<p>The Hollywood and content community are attending CES in larger numbers to experience new devices, technologies and platforms in one place, at one event, to see where content will play next. <em>Variety </em>will be producing the <em>Official CES Entertainment Matters Daily</em> for the 2013 International CES. Dedicated to Entertainment Matters programming, news, events, announcements and special features, you&rsquo;ll have firsthand access to the most important news and announcements impacting the entertainment industry at CES. Advertising is available &ndash; for more information, please contact <em>Variety&rsquo;s</em> Andi Elliott at <a href="mailto:andi.elliott@variety.com">andi.elliott@variety.com</a> | 301-774-6874.</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="725"><span style="display: none">Increase Your Company Visibility and Exposure on CES Mobile</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Increase Your Company Visibility and Exposure on CES Mobile</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/CES%20Mobile%20App/CESMobile120x120.jpg"/>
<p>Upload your press kit, press releases, brochures, and any other material handouts, along with your company logo, onto the <a href="http://www.cesweb.org/cesmobile" target="_blank">2013 CES Mobile App</a> for FREE!<br />
<br />
Purchase the QR Code Builder &amp; Leads Package from your CES Mobile Exhibitor Portal. All attendees are provided with a QR code reader built directly into CES Mobile making it easy to scan exhibitor QR codes. The QR Code Builder &amp; Leads Package enables you to build QR codes that deliver your company and product information to these users when they scan your QR code or visit your Exhibitor Listing within the app. In return, you receive the app usage/leads information of these previously &ldquo;un-captured&rdquo; leads.<br />
<br />
View more <a href="http://cesweb.org/For-Exhibitors/Promotional-Opportunities/Sponsorships.aspx?#36" target="_blank">CES Mobile promotional opportunities</a>. For more information please contact Collin Tokosch at ces2013@core-apps.com</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="726"><span style="display: none">Maximize Your Exposure with Advertising in It Is Innovation (i3)</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Maximize Your Exposure with Advertising in It Is Innovation (i3)</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/newsletter/attendee/i3.gif"/>
<p>The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA)<sup>&reg;</sup> is relaunching its flagship publication (previously called <a href="http://www.cevision.org/" target="_blank"><em>Consumer Electronics Vision</em></a> magazine) under the new name <a href="http://www.ce.org/CorporateSite/media/CEA-Publications/I3-MediaKit_082012.pdf" target="_blank"><strong><em>It Is Innovation (i<sup>3</sup>)</em></strong></a>. The inaugural issue will debut at the <a href="http://www.cesweb.org" target="_blank">2013 International CES<sup>&reg;</sup></a> in January. Don&rsquo;t miss your opportunity to take advantage of special introductory advertising rates at CES and <strong>all year long</strong>!<br />
<br />
<em>i<sup>3</sup></em> will highlight the entrepreneurial spirit of the consumer electronics (CE) industry &mdash; the constant innovations in design, engineering, software, manufacturing processes, unique business and retail models and marketing platforms &mdash; all of the things that make our industry special. Readers include the professionals that design, manufacture, buy, distribute and analyze products and trends for this $206 billion industry &mdash; the core of the International CES.<br />
<br />
<strong>With <em>i<sup>3</sup></em>, your company can:</strong><br />
&bull; Increase your visibility at CES<br />
&bull; Position your brand as an innovative category leader<br />
&bull; Support the industry and CEA<br />
&bull; Reach 49,000 domestic and 12,000 international readers<br />
&bull; Connect with Washington policymakers<br />
<br />
To learn more about advertising opportunities, contact <a href="mailto:DCole@CE.org?subject=i3%20Inquiry%20from%20December%20Partner%20Connection">Dan Cole</a> at 703-907-7987 or download the <a href="http://www.ce.org/CorporateSite/media/CEA-Publications/I3-MediaKit_082012.pdf" target="_blank">media kit</a>.</p>
<br><br>
<hr class="separator">
<br>
<a name="731"><span style="display: none">Gain the Attention of Leading Imaging Buyers and Professional Photographers</span></a>
<div class="sub-content-header">Gain the Attention of Leading Imaging Buyers and Professional Photographers</div><br/>
<img style ='float: right; margin: 0 5px 5px 5px;' src="/cesweb/media/CESWeb/TechZones/CES_TZ_PMA_200.jpg"/>
<p>If you have a product or service that is digital imaging/photography related and you want to catch the eye of the top buyers in the industry, including photographers, look no further than the PMA events. PMA@CES Conference and exhibits will take place at the LVH during the 2013 International CES. <a href="http://www.pmai.org/PMA_CES.aspx?id=22214" target="_blank">Promotional opportunities</a> are available in and around the Paradise Center, home of PMA@CES exhibits. &nbsp;<br />
<br />
You may also be interested in the <a href="http://www.pmai.org/PMA_CES.aspx?id=21838" target="_blank">DIMA and PSPA/SPAA Conferences</a>, to be held January 6-7, 2013 at Bally&rsquo;s Las Vegas, the most important and relevant educational and networking event for the photo imaging industry. Promote your company and products to a focused audience of digital imaging/photography professionals through a variety of sponsorship opportunities. Stand out from the crowd with a Platinum sponsorship; sponsor a session or break, or take part in the Vendor Reception.<br />
<br />
Act now while opportunities still exist. Contact <a href="mailto:jfrazine@pmai.org?subject=Conference%20Sponsorship%20Information">Jeff Frazine</a> (517) 788-8100 x101 for more information or to secure your place in front of the imaging buyers today!</p>
